Headlines.Headline: Noble Corp. 3Q Profit Jumps 57% On Contract Extensions

PARAGRAPH.#text: Noble Corp. NE posted Wednesday a 57% increase in its third-quarter profit as the contract driller reported improving demand. "We are witnessing an intensified effort by a number of customers to secure jackup and floating rigs for drilling operations in 2012 and beyond, supporting higher fleet utilization and improving dayrates," Chairman and Chief Executive David Williams said, adding that the company's floating rig fleet also is seeing higher demand, especially among ultra-deepwater rigs. Along with its peers in the contract-drilling sector, Noble is poised to benefit from a broad-based recovery in day rates.

PARAGRAPH.#text: More stocks to watch this morning, courtesy of our friends at Dow Jones.Boston Scientific Corp. swung to a first-quarter profit following a steep $1.84 billion write-down last year, as the medical-device maker reported higher cardiac-rhythm management product sales in the latest period but lower stent sales. Shares rose 3.8% to $7.35 in after-hours trading, as the adjusted bottom line figure topped the company's expectations.Select Comfort Corp.'s first-quarter earnings more than doubled, topping the company's own estimates, as the mattress seller saw a jump in sales and improved margins. Shares rose sharply after hours, up 21% in recent trading to $16.07.Cheesecake Factory Inc.'s first-quarter profit jumped 9.6%, narrowly beating its own downbeat estimate, as the casual-dining company posted its fifth straight quarter of increased same-store sales. Shares shed 2.6% to $29.80 in late trading.American Express Co. said customers increased their spending by 17% in the latest quarter and losses from souring card loans further receded, leading net income to rise 33% to a new first-quarter record. Still, shares slipped 1.5% to $46.32 in after-hours trading.Honeywell International Inc.'s first-quarter profit jumped 44% as sales rose across all its business lines, Shares rose 1.5% to $59.60 in recent after-hours trading as the results topped the company's expectations and the company boosted its guidance.Noble Corp.'s first-quarter earnings plunged 85% as results were again slammed by restrictions on drilling in the Gulf of Mexico. Shares were down 5% at $41.25 in after-hours trading.Terex Corp.'s first-quarter profit slumped 98% absent a big prior-year asset sale gain, although the equipment maker reported sales growth that exceeded Wall Street's expectations and higher gross margins. Shares of the company, which makes specialized equipment such as tower cranes and rock crushers, climbed 3.5% to $33.82 in late trading.Tractor Supply Co.'s first-quarter earnings rose 73% on strong sales of animal- and pet-related merchandise, along with seasonal goods. The results easily topped analysts' expectations. Shares traded 2.1% higher at $64.32 after hours.

Headlines.Headline: Noble 2Q Earnings Up 4.3% On Higher Contract Drilling Revenue

#text: DOW JONES NEWSWIRES Noble Corp.'s

second-quarter profit improved 4.3% due to higher contract-drilling services revenue, which offset lower margins and a charge. The offshore-drilling contractor has reported steady profit growth, despite volatility in energy prices and plunging demand. Chief Executive David W. Williams said Noble doesn't expect the near-term contracting environment to change significantly despite the gradual recovery in crude prices.
